&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Batch Changes&lt;/strong&gt; - our battle-tested execution layer for massive cross-repo changes helps developers automate large-scale code changes across all of an enterprise&#39;s repositories: keeping code up-to-date, fixing critical security issues, and paying down tech debt, with every change tracked through checks and code review until it merges. Teams at Stripe, Uber, Dropbox, Lyft, Reddit, and others use it to drive migrations, refactors, and security fixes. Building on this product, we’re working toward an agent in the outer-loop to turn a prompt into a staged, self-healing rollout, complete with CI feedback loops and post-publish remediation.&lt;/li&gt;
